TV Remote.definition: a device that can be used to control a machine or apparatus from a distance

Medicine Pill.definition: something that resembles a tablet of medicine in shape or size

Cordless Phone.definition: electronic equipment that converts sound into electrical signals that can be transmitted over distances and then converts received signals back into sounds

Prescription Bottle.definition: a glass or plastic vessel used for storing drinks or other liquids; typically cylindrical without handles and with a narrow neck that can be plugged or capped

Fork.definition: cutlery used for serving and eating food

Glasses.definition: optical instrument consisting of a frame that holds a pair of lenses for correcting defective vision

Toothbrush.definition: small brush; has long handle; used to clean teeth

Spoon.definition: a piece of cutlery with a shallow bowl-shaped container and a handle; used to stir or serve or take up food

Cell Phone.definition: electronic equipment that converts sound into electrical signals that can be transmitted over distances and then converts received signals back into sounds

Toothpaste.definition: a dentifrice in the form of a paste

Book.definition: a written work or composition that has been published (printed on pages bound together)

Hand Towel.definition: a rectangular piece of absorbent cloth (or paper) for drying or wiping

Mail.definition: the bags of letters and packages that are transported by the postal service

Cup.definition: the quantity that can be held in a mug

Soap.definition: a cleansing agent made from the salts of vegetable or animal fats

Disposable Bottle.definition: a glass or plastic vessel used for storing drinks or other liquids; typically cylindrical without handles and with a narrow neck that can be plugged or capped

Shoe.definition: footwear shaped to fit the foot (below the ankle) with a flexible upper of leather or plastic and a sole and heel of heavier material

Dish Bowl.definition: a round vessel that is open at the top; used chiefly for holding food or liquids

Keys.definition: metal device shaped in such a way that when it is inserted into the appropriate lock the lock's mechanism can be rotated

Dish Plate.definition: (baseball) base consisting of a rubber slab where the batter stands; it must be touched by a base runner in order to score

Pencil.definition: a thin cylindrical pointed writing implement; a rod of marking substance encased in wood

Table Knife.definition: edge tool used as a cutting instrument; has a pointed blade with a sharp edge and a handle

Credit Card.definition: one of a set of small pieces of stiff paper marked in various ways and used for playing games or for telling fortunes

Medicine Box.definition: a (usually rectangular) container; may have a lid

Bill.definition: a statute in draft before it becomes law

Straw.definition: plant fiber used e.g. for making baskets and hats or as fodder

Magazine.definition: a periodic publication containing pictures and stories and articles of interest to those who purchase it or subscribe to it

Plastic Container.definition: any object that can be used to hold things (especially a large metal boxlike object of standardized dimensions that can be loaded from one form of transport to another)

Newspaper.definition: a daily or weekly publication on folded sheets; contains news and articles and advertisements

Non-disposable Bottle.definition: a glass or plastic vessel used for storing drinks or other liquids; typically cylindrical without handles and with a narrow neck that can be plugged or capped

Shirt.definition: a garment worn on the upper half of the body

Wallet.definition: a pocket-size case for holding papers and paper money

Small Pillow.definition: a cushion to support the head of a sleeping person

Socks.definition: hosiery consisting of a cloth covering for the foot; worn inside the shoe; reaches to between the ankle and the knee

Hairbrush.definition: a brush used to groom a person's hair

Can.definition: airtight sealed metal container for food or drink or paint etc.

Coins.definition: a flat metal piece (usually a disc) used as money

Walking Cane.definition: a stick that people can lean on to help them walk

Scissors.definition: an edge tool having two crossed pivoting blades

Purse.definition: a container used for carrying money and small personal items or accessories (especially by women)

Lighter.definition: a substance used to ignite or kindle a fire
